1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:20,000
Solana event merch still trades through DMs and trust. Merchplace makes those trades escrowed, trackable, and event-specific.

2
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Sellers list event merch. Buyers deposit USDC into escrow. Sellers add tracking. Buyers release funds when the item arrives.

3
00:00:40,000 --> 00:01:20,000
Seller flow: create a listing with event context, photos, price, and carrier shipping. Metadata goes live after backend verification.

4
00:01:20,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Buyer flow: open the listing, review escrow math and risk notes, buy the item, and watch the status move to in escrow.

5
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:25,000
Fulfillment flow: seller adds tracking, buyer reviews delivery context, then confirms receipt to release funds.

6
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:50,000
Technical proof: Anchor program functions and localnet smoke tests cover create, buy, confirm, buyer cancellation, and seller cancellation.

7
00:02:50,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Merchplace is starting with Breakpoint and Colosseum drops, then expanding to Superteam and Solana event shelves.
